narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Really interesting, fun, easy-going curriculum. A lot of exams, but it is never unmanageable. Try to get a smaller class--it gives a better atmosphere.

120 gets a bit trickier than 110, but it covers the material at a much nicer (read: slower) pace than 110 does. There are more movies and we even read a short story! Definitely would recommend it, especially if you can get Chris.
AWESOME . TOTALLY RECOMMENDED. Italian department rocks
Take this course with Chris Kaiser.
I would say that it is a great class and other students should definitely take it. It is not a gut class and you have to work a little, but it is a lot of fun and you learn a ton.
If you want a language credit, the Italian department is fantastic. It's a challenging course, but very fun and engaging nonetheless.

As follows:ITAL 120 is a continuation of ITAL 110, that is to say, a class that introduces the basic grammatical concepts of Italian in a fast-paced but well-regulated manner spiced plentifully with cultural tibits and interactive exercises.
